SECTION 4: ENFORCEMENT & LIQUIDATED DAMAGES
================================================================================

4.1 AUTOMATED COMPLIANCE VERIFICATION

The Software contains automated compliance verification mechanisms that detect
the deployment environment. These mechanisms collect ONLY the following
non-personal metadata for license compliance purposes:

  - System hostname (anonymized hash)
  - Network domain classification (corporate/individual)
  - Timestamp of verification
  - Software version

4.2 CONSENT TO MONITORING

By downloading, installing, or executing any component of this Software,
the user consents to automated compliance verification as described in
Section 4.1.

4.3 LIQUIDATED DAMAGES

Any Corporate Entity that deploys, uses, or executes this Software without
a valid Commercial License Key agrees to the following liquidated damages,
which the parties agree represent a reasonable estimate of the Licensor's
actual damages:

  (a) USD $150,000 per instance of unauthorized deployment.
  (b) USD $50,000 per month of continued unauthorized use.
  (c) Reimbursement of all legal fees incurred in enforcement.

4.4 COMPLIANCE REPORTING

Upon detection of unauthorized Corporate use, the Software may generate a
timestamped compliance report containing only anonymized technical metadata
(no personal data). This report may be archived to establish a record of
the violation for legal proceedings.

4.5 INJUNCTIVE RELIEF

The Licensor reserves the right to seek injunctive relief in addition to
liquidated damages for any unauthorized use.

